# prototype-builder — environment variables
#
# The bare scaffold on `main` does not require any secrets. Prototypes that
# call external APIs (LLMs, databases, payments, etc.) may need keys listed
# in your spec.
#
# ── Local development ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Copy this file (gitignored destination):
#      cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Uncomment and fill in only the keys your prototype uses.
# 3. Restart `npm run dev` after changes.
#
# ── Cursor Background Agent (cloud runs) ────────────────────────────────────
# Add the same variable names in Cursor → Settings → Background Agents →
# Secrets. Agents read them as process.env.* — never commit real values.
#
# ── Vercel preview / production ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Preview + Production as needed).
# To sync Vercel env into a local file for debugging:
#      npx vercel env pull .env.local
#
# Reference in code via process.env.VAR_NAME only. Never log secret values.

# ── Example keys (uncomment as needed) ──────────────────────────────────────

# LLM / AI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Database (Neon, Supabase, etc. via Vercel Marketplace)
# DATABASE_URL=

# Auth (Clerk, Auth0, etc.)
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Public client config — safe for the browser; never put secrets here
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
